      "content": "thanks, that makes sense for a western context. but i'm trying to make this guide for a global audience. \n\nhow do you handle it when someone's native or traditional attire doesn't fit those \"classic\" western suit or dress standards? like if a professional in an east asian or african country wants to incorporate more of their own cultural heritage into their look while staying \"sophisticated\" and meeting these global standards you mentioned? do they need to adjust to fit the \"gold standard\" to be taken seriously?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
